entries.meaning: a tabular schedule of events with the times at which they occur, especially times of arrivals and departures
examples: The timetable has been changed several times since it was first announced.

entries.meaning: A schedule of arrivals and departures published in book or booklet form, or as a pamphlet, and available to travellers, either free or for a charge.

verbs.description: timetable (third-person singular simple present timetables, present participle timetabling, simple past and past participle timetabled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To arrange a specific time for (an event, a class, etc).
examples: I've timetabled the meeting for Monday afternoon.
